Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1

The addSecs() function is already very, very, bad API since it sounds as if it would modify *this, but actually returns a new object. We had actual bugs because of this in KDE that were only found when GCC started to actually warn about complex unused return types.

Please don't add more.

I'd suggest to deprecate addSecs(), too, and instead add op+ and op+= (and -, -=) taking std::chrono::milliseconds, which will allow

   dt = dt + 1h + 30m;
   dt += 1h + 30m;
